	&lt;li additional=&quot;&quot; align-items:=&quot;&quot; answer=&quot;&quot; cdn.testbook.com=&quot;&quot; certain=&quot;&quot; color:=&quot;&quot; correct=&quot;&quot; data-end=&quot;&quot; data-start=&quot;&quot; differences=&quot;&quot; display:=&quot;&quot; due=&quot;&quot; em=&quot;&quot; fiscal=&quot;&quot; font-size:=&quot;&quot; font-weight:=&quot;&quot; gap:=&quot;&quot; height=&quot;&quot; his=&quot;&quot; img=&quot;&quot; in=&quot;&quot; is=&quot;&quot; jawaharlal=&quot;&quot; k=&quot;&quot; li=&quot;&quot; lms_creative_elements=&quot;&quot; over=&quot;&quot; prime=&quot;&quot; r=&quot;&quot; resignation=&quot;&quot; resources=&quot;&quot; shanmugham=&quot;&quot; span=&quot;&quot; src=&quot;&quot; statement=&quot;&quot; style=&quot;&quot; the=&quot;&quot; then=&quot;&quot; to=&quot;&quot; vertical-align:=&quot;&quot; was=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;&quot; with=&quot;&quot;&gt;Chetty was born in &lt;strong&gt;1892&lt;/strong&gt; in &lt;strong&gt;Coimbatore, Tamil Nadu&lt;/strong&gt;. He was a &lt;strong&gt;lawyer by profession&lt;/strong&gt; and later became a successful industrialist.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li a=&quot;&quot; and=&quot;&quot; as=&quot;&quot; becoming=&quot;&quot; before=&quot;&quot; capacities=&quot;&quot; data-end=&quot;&quot; data-start=&quot;&quot; delegate=&quot;&quot; finance=&quot;&quot; he=&quot;&quot; held=&quot;&quot; in=&quot;&quot; including=&quot;&quot; legislative=&quot;&quot; li=&quot;&quot; madras=&quot;&quot; member=&quot;&quot; of=&quot;&quot; round=&quot;&quot; served=&quot;&quot; table=&quot;&quot; the=&quot;&quot; to=&quot;&quot; various=&quot;&quot;&gt;Chetty&amp;#39;s contribution to shaping India&amp;#39;s early economic policies was significant, particularly during a time when the country faced enormous challenges post-independence.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Other Options:&lt;/strong&gt;

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;John Mathai:&lt;/strong&gt; He succeeded R K Shanmugham Chetty as the second Finance Minister of India. He presented the &lt;strong&gt;Union Budget of 1949-50&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
